From: John Jacques <john.jacques@lsi.com>
Date: Mon, 24 Mar 2014 14:24:34 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 56/71] arch/powerpc: Fix Compile Error when the Target is
 PowerPC

git://git.yoctoproject.org/linux-yocto-3.10 standard/axxia/base
commit afcf631998853611f497214da5b99635860b0dea

Recent LSI GPDMA driver updates, tested on ARM, broke the build
on PowerPC.  Including linux/sizes.h fixes the error.

Signed-off-by: John Jacques <john.jacques@lsi.com>
Signed-off-by: Zhong Hongbo <hongbo.zhong@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/dma/lsi-dma32.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/dma/lsi-dma32.c b/drivers/dma/lsi-dma32.c
index c874d85..3490788 100644
--- a/drivers/dma/lsi-dma32.c
+++ b/drivers/dma/lsi-dma32.c
@@ -36,6 +36,7 @@
 #include <asm/page.h>
 #include <linux/bitops.h>
 #include <linux/atomic.h>
+#include <linux/sizes.h>
 #include "virt-dma.h"
 #include "lsi-dma32.h"
 
